==<center><big><big>'''Description + Usage'''</big></big></center>==
[[File:51.png|thumb|336x436px]]
'''Object 53''' is an empty and lone vending machine that can be found with a spotlight on top. This vending machine works functionally, with coin dispensers and item slots. The vending machine is filled with drinks and refreshments. The drinks are fruity with special effects and have transportation powers.

Buying a drink and leaving it on the floor, then walking away, will make the drink reappear in your hands. If you put it back again, the same effect happens over and over again. Some drinks are based on real brands from '''[[The Frontrooms]]''' like Coca-Cola, Pepsi, Sprite, Fanta, etc. These drinks have no effects and just hydrate the wanderer. Here are the special effects from the fruity drinks:
==<center><big><big>'''Variants'''</big></big></center>==
==<center><big><big>'''The Plum Treat'''</big></big></center>==
[[File:Plum51.png|thumb|left|336x436px]]<div style="text-align:right;">
'''The Plum Treat''' is part of '''Object 53'''. Drinking a plum treat will teleport you to a dark series of green-like hallways resembling '''[[Level 5]]'''. The main colors are the colors of plums. Plants, chairs, and objects float around the hallways. Touching any chairs will make you lose your collision forever.

There's a chance that the chairs will chase you around the hallways, so any wanderer who ends up here will have to run faster than the chairs.<ref>(They go faster than Usain Bolt)</ref> Certain holes in the walls can be any size. This is a wanderer's only chance to escape '''The Plum Treat''', but the wanderer will be sent to '''[[The Void]]'''... This area is the largest area of '''Object 53''', due to '''The Plum Treat''' being the largest fruit available.</div>
==<center><big><big>'''The Strawberry Treat'''</big></big></center>==
[[File:Strawberry51.png|right|336x436px]]<div style="text-align:left;">
'''The Strawberry Treat''' is part of '''Object 53'''. A wanderer could be forced to eat '''The Strawberry Treat''' due to it looking the prettiest, even though the wanderer most likely wouldn't want to. As soon as the wanderer smells the crisp and tart flavor, the wanderer will be teleported to '''The Strawberry Treat'''.

You will be sent to an infinite field representing '''[[Level 55]]''' filled with houses. The skies are pink, and an ominous buzz deafens the wanderer. A wanderer cannot stay in the pink skies for too long, but a wanderer needs to find shelter in one of the houses. It is recommended to find shelter before nighttime. After nighttime, [[Entity 3|something will find YOU.]]<ref>That is, if you're still outside.</ref>

<div style="text-align: right;"><span class="mw-customtoggle-final3 mw-customtoggle-initial3"><div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-initial3">
<center>You enter a house. One of them is occupied..</center></div></span>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-final3">
<div class="mw-customtoggle-final3 mw-customtoggle-initial3">
<center>You enter a house. One of them is occupied..</center></div>
</div></div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-final3">
=<center><big>This house is occupied.</big></center>=
<hr><hr><div style="text-align:center;">
This house wasn't empty.

A knife pierces your chest as you cough blood, and your teeth fall onto the carpeted floor.

The survivor that lives here mistook you for an entity.

Your path ends so pathetically like this.

Blood mixes with strawberry flavor.
[[File:Occupied51.png|center|thumb|406x406px]]</div></div>

==<center><big><big>'''The Coconut Treat'''</big></big></center>==
[[File:Coconut51.png|thumb|left|336x436px]]<div style="text-align:right;">
'''The Coconut Treat''' is part of '''Object 53'''. '''The Coconut Treat''' will spawn the wanderer into an open, white room with a head that has just spawned behind the wanderer. If a wanderer walks away and takes another bite, another head will spawn; this time, in front of you. A wanderer can keep doing this, and more and more heads will keep spawning.

If a wanderer throws '''The Coconut Treat''' in the trash can near the wanderer, tons of heads will spawn in front of the wanderer, making this an eternal purgatory. The heads block off the door behind them, and if you try to go through, they will kill the wanderer until no remains are left. Then, another wanderer eats '''The Coconut Treat''', and the same cycle loops indefinitely.

Chewing the tiniest bit of '''The Coconut Treat''' will teleport a wanderer to a castle filled with untrustworthy signs. The head is still behind you. The castle could be a wanderer's only exit. Try to escape? If a wanderer walks away from the castle, you will find a road to another level. A wanderer could recognize the lights beyond the rails. The wanderer's home is near! Outside [[The Backrooms]]! When the wanderer steps on the rail, a train comes and will run the wanderer over.

[[File:SoClose51.png|center|thumb|600x600px]]
==<center><big><big>'''Alternate Strawberry Treat'''</big></big></center>==
[[File:AltStrawberry51.png|thumb|336x436px]]<div style="text-align:left;">
You can enter the '''Alternate Strawberry Treat''' by entering the dark castle and finding the '''Alternate Strawberry Treat'''. The '''Alternate Strawberry Treat''' is like '''The Strawberry Treat''', but it is dark and a roof is on top of the level instead of a sky. The next level is under the pinkish roof. The roof crushes the top of houses, trees, and at the end, the wanderer's bones.

A wanderer can also enter the '''Alternate Strawberry Treat''' during nighttime in '''The Strawberry Treat''', although this is a 1 in 100 chance. Other than that, the '''[[Entity 3|Smilers]]''' will tear the wanderer up. This is not a strawberry; this is a ■■■■■■■ ■■■■■■...  Do not even eat this fruit. Would you eat the fruit or be stuck in the castle forever?<ref>It's a choice.</ref>
==<center><big><big>'''The Lime Treat'''</big></big></center>==
[[File:Lime51.png|thumb|left|336x436px]]<div style="text-align:right;">
'''The Lime Treat''' is part of '''Object 53'''. If a wanderer picks '''The Lime Treat''', the wanderer will gain the power of night vision. The wanderer will be sent to a green/lime-like hallway shown in the image. It appears to be a prison. The wanderer can enter different levels using cages in the prison and can wander into the darker levels, aside from '''[[Level 6]]'''. The prison has food and supplies to help the wanderer on '''[[The Backrooms|this journey]]'''. There are no entities in this area.

After a while of having this night-vision effect, the wanderer will soon regret it and wish they could take their eyes out. They will never find a vending machine again, so the wanderer cannot undo the effect.
==<center><big><big>'''Unknown Fruit Treat'''</big></big></center>==
[[File:Unknown51.png|thumb|336x436px]]<div style="text-align:left;">
The '''Unknown Fruit Treat''' is unlabeled and dipped in black ganache. Most wanderers are tempted to try this fruit due to it not being a "fruit". If the wanderer eats the fruit, your vision adjusts; all the previous levels were an illusion. These neon-colored hallways have always been there. The wanderer broke the simulation. They're free?

The '''Unknown Fruit Treat''' represents an infinite neon cinema. When a wanderer eats the fruit, the movie number starts at 1. It goes all the way to infinity. That is the wanderer's only exit to '''[[The Frontrooms]]'''. This exit is only theorized and not possible due to it holding the impossible exit to '''[[The Frontrooms]]'''. The neon cinema illuminates the wanderer..
==<center><big><big>'''Bittersweet Fruit Treat'''</big></big></center>==
[[File:Overslept.png|thumb|center|336x436px]]<div style="text-align:center;">

...


Welcome back.


I'm sorry we couldn't find the exit in [[The Backrooms]].


I'm relieved you made it safely.


[[w:c:backrooms:Object_53|Oh, you wanna retry..]]
